						<summary>

						<p>On a slab near the māḷa quarters.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1133, Pramōdūta</hi> corresponding to 1210 A.D., (Śaka Year is 1132.)</p>						

						<p>It records the gift of land by Mēluganti Komara Nāyaka and his brothers to the trikūṭa (temple) erected by them at Bradukīsvaram in the names of Gaṇapati their master and Koṇḍa Nāyaka and Mailasāni, their parents.</p>						

						</summary>
